        <!-- Main Content -->
        <main class="main-content">
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <!-- Left Content -->
                <div class="content-left">
                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>About 10th CBSE/NCERT</h2>
                        <p>The Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) is one of the most popular education boards in India. The National Council of Educational Research and Training (NCERT) is responsible for designing the curriculum and textbooks for CBSE schools. The 10th CBSE/NCERT syllabus is designed to provide a strong foundation for students and prepare them for higher education.</p>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <p>The 10th CBSE/NCERT curriculum focuses on core subjects like Mathematics, Science, Social Science, English, and Hindi. It emphasizes conceptual understanding, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>10th CBSE/NCERT Subjects</h2>
                        <p>The 10th CBSE/NCERT curriculum includes the following subjects:</p>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Mathematics:</strong> Algebra, Geometry, Trigonometry, Statistics, and Probability.</li>
                                <li><strong>Science:</strong> Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.</li>
                                <li><strong>Social Science:</strong> History, Geography, Political Science, and Economics.</li>
                                <li><strong>English:</strong> Literature, Grammar, and Writing Skills.</li>
                                <li><strong>Hindi:</strong> Literature, Grammar, and Writing Skills.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>10th CBSE/NCERT Syllabus</h2>
                        <p>The 10th CBSE/NCERT syllabus is designed to provide a comprehensive understanding of each subject. Below is a brief overview of the syllabus:</p>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h3>Mathematics</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Real Numbers</li>
                                <li>Polynomials</li>
                                <li>Pair of Linear Equations in Two Variables</li>
                                <li>Quadratic Equations</li>
                                <li>Arithmetic Progressions</li>
                                <li>Triangles</li>
                                <li>Coordinate Geometry</li>
                                <li>Trigonometry</li>
                                <li>Circles</li>
                                <li>Constructions</li>
                                <li>Areas Related to Circles</li>
                                <li>Surface Areas and Volumes</li>
                                <li>Statistics and Probability</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h3>Science</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Chemical Reactions and Equations</li>
                                <li>Acids, Bases, and Salts</li>
                                <li>Metals and Non-Metals</li>
                                <li>Carbon and Its Compounds</li>
                                <li>Periodic Classification of Elements</li>
                                <li>Life Processes</li>
                                <li>Control and Coordination</li>
                                <li>How Do Organisms Reproduce?</li>
                                <li>Heredity and Evolution</li>
                                <li>Light – Reflection and Refraction</li>
                                <li>Human Eye and Colourful World</li>
                                <li>Electricity</li>
                                <li>Magnetic Effects of Electric Current</li>
                                <li>Sources of Energy</li>
                                <li>Our Environment</li>
                                <li>Management of Natural Resources</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h3>Social Science</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>History: The Rise of Nationalism in Europe, Nationalism in India, etc.</li>
                                <li>Geography: Resources and Development, Water Resources, Agriculture, etc.</li>
                                <li>Political Science: Power Sharing, Federalism, Democracy and Diversity, etc.</li>
                                <li>Economics: Development, Sectors of the Indian Economy, Money and Credit, etc.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>Preparation Tips for 10th CBSE/NCERT</h2>
                        <p>Here are some tips to help you prepare effectively for the 10th CBSE/NCERT exams:</p>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Understand the Syllabus:</strong> Go through the syllabus thoroughly and prioritize topics based on their weightage.</li>
                                <li><strong>Practice Regularly:</strong> Solve sample papers and previous years' question papers to improve your problem-solving skills.</li>
                                <li><strong>Focus on Concepts:</strong> Focus on understanding concepts rather than rote learning.</li>
                                <li><strong>Time Management:</strong> Create a study schedule and allocate time for each subject.</li>
                                <li><strong>Revise Regularly:</strong> Revise regularly to retain what you have learned.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Right Content (Form) -->
                <div class="content-right">
                    <form class="enquiry-form" id="enquiryForm" action="/submit-cbseTest" method="POST">
                        <h3>Planning to study abroad?</h3>
                        <p>Get free 1-on-1 counselling with our experts</p>
            
